definitions.definition: The daughter of Catreus, king of Crete, and sister to Clymene, Apemosyne and Althaemenes. Catreus gave her to Nauplius, to be drowned or sold abroad, but Nauplius spared her.
A daughter of Cepheus of Arcadia, who was king of Tegea.
